# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen6Hinterlands
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "This was where the main road split off into the Hinterlands, the far-removed backwater provinces of Rosanna."
    new "This was where the main road split off into the Hinterlands, the far-removed backwater provinces of Rosanna."

    old "Watching the dire condition of the road, Sarah wondered if she had not made a mistake."
    new "Watching the dire condition of the road, Sarah wondered if she had not made a mistake."

    old "Regardless, it was too late to stop now."
    new "Regardless, it was too late to stop now."

    old "Her army headed off towards the Hinterlands, leaving the main road behind."
    new "Her army headed off towards the Hinterlands, leaving the main road behind."

    old "At first, the soldiers continued to march on the road that led into the Hinterlands."
    new "At first, the soldiers continued to march on the road that led into the Hinterlands."

    old "But soon, the quality of the road declined so much, that their metal boots cracked the earth and turned it to mud."
    new "But soon, the quality of the road declined so much, that their metal boots cracked the earth and turned it to mud."

    old "The wagons, carrying the army supplies found their wheels caught in the deep mud, slowing the march."
    new "The wagons, carrying the army supplies found their wheels caught in the deep mud, slowing the march."

    old "As some wagons sank into the mud, others became stuck behind them."
    new "As some wagons sank into the mud, others became stuck behind them."

    old "The soldiers were instructed to march besides the road, leaving the road proper only for the wagons."
    new "The soldiers were instructed to march besides the road, leaving the road proper only for the wagons."

    old "It improved their situation, but only by so much."
    new "It improved their situation, but only by so much."

    old "The soldiers themselves, now forced to march through the fields, thick with snow, struggled."
    new "The soldiers themselves, now forced to march through the fields, thick with snow, struggled."

    old "Cold winds assaulted them for every mile they crossed."
    new "Cold winds assaulted them for every mile they crossed."

    old "And as far as the horizon, nothing but vast fields of blinding white snow."
    new "And as far as the horizon, nothing but vast fields of blinding white snow."

    old "Two days in these miserable conditions."
    new "Two days in these miserable conditions."

    old "Two days of suffering the elements, before her army came upon the nearest place that could be called a town."
    new "Two days of suffering the elements, before her army came upon the nearest place that could be called a town."

    old "A brief respite. A chance to restock."
    new "A brief respite. A chance to restock."

    old "Her army marched into the town, stunned and confused peasants looking on."
    new "Her army marched into the town, stunned and confused peasants looking on."

    old "Sarah made her way into the town's tavern."
    new "Sarah made her way into the town's tavern."

    old "Most of her soldiers would have to make camp outside of the town. The lucky few could find a hovel to rent for the night."
    new "Most of her soldiers would have to make camp outside of the town. The lucky few could find a hovel to rent for the night."

    old "Sarah sat down in the tavern."
    new "Sarah sat down in the tavern."

    old "Around her, commanders swarming, planning, advising."
    new "Around her, commanders swarming, planning, advising."

    old "Their plans, only days old, had already been delayed."
    new "Their plans, only days old, had already been delayed."

    old "The roads were worse than she had feared. The elements harsher."
    new "The roads were worse than she had feared. The elements harsher."

    old "A nervous innkeeper came up to her table and served her some beer and food."
    new "A nervous innkeeper came up to her table and served her some beer and food."

    old "No...it's nothing, really...my honor to serve..."
    new "No...it's nothing, really...my honor to serve..."

    old "His voice trembled."
    new "His voice trembled."

    old "Nothing, nothing. Forgive me, your Grace."
    new "Nothing, nothing. Forgive me, your Grace."

    old "The man stumbled away."
    new "The man stumbled away."

    old "Sarah followed him with her eyes, unsure of what to make of the strange innkeeper."
    new "Sarah followed him with her eyes, unsure of what to make of the strange innkeeper."

    old "Sitting around the table, Sarah held court as an endless stream of commanders and officers pleaded for her attention."
    new "Sitting around the table, Sarah held court as an endless stream of commanders and officers pleaded for her attention."

    old "For every issue she solved, two others would be dropped in her lap."
    new "For every issue she solved, two others would be dropped in her lap."

    old "Sarah looked over and saw Samayra, argueing with a few officers, telling them stay away."
    new "Sarah looked over and saw Samayra, argueing with a few officers, telling them stay away."

    old "Sarah smiled, happy that she at least had Samayra, a capable secretary that could keep her schedule manageable."
    new "Sarah smiled, happy that she at least had Samayra, a capable secretary that could keep her schedule manageable."

    old "It was late into the night when a group of about four men stumbled into the tavern."
    new "It was late into the night when a group of about four men stumbled into the tavern."

    old "Sarah frowned as she watched them stumble inside, shouting loudly."
    new "Sarah frowned as she watched them stumble inside, shouting loudly."

    old "Hail Sarah Rose!"
    new "Hail Sarah Rose!"

    old "Second man\" \"She'll show those Savages!"
    new "Second man\" \"She'll show those Savages!"

    old "The men stumbled further into the room, the guards held them at a distance."
    new "The men stumbled further into the room, the guards held them at a distance."

    old "Hey! No need to fight us, we're just here to celebrate her Highness!"
    new "Hey! No need to fight us, we're just here to celebrate her Highness!"

    old "The man raised a flask filled with something that reeked of strong alcohol."
    new "The man raised a flask filled with something that reeked of strong alcohol."

    old "Sarah slightly nodded, acknowledging the man without hoping to encourage him."
    new "Sarah slightly nodded, acknowledging the man without hoping to encourage him."

    old "Second man\" \"Ay! Cheers to that!"
    new "Second man\" \"Ay! Cheers to that!"

    old "Second man\" \"Finally someone that's gonna return the King's Law to these lands!"
    new "Second man\" \"Finally someone that's gonna return the King's Law to these lands!"

    old "Second man\" \"Or the Queen's Law, my lady, apologies!"
    new "Second man\" \"Or the Queen's Law, my lady, apologies!"

    old "He raised his drink along with this friends."
    new "He raised his drink along with this friends."

    old "Speaking of justice and law! I would wish to pe...pet...peti..."
    new "Speaking of justice and law! I would wish to pe...pet...peti..."

    old "Second man\" \"Petition."
    new "Second man\" \"Petition."

    old "Petition! I would like to petition the Court!"
    new "Petition! I would like to petition the Court!"

    old "It had been a long tradition that the people of Rosanna were permitted to offer up their grievances to their king or queen."
    new "It had been a long tradition that the people of Rosanna were permitted to offer up their grievances to their king or queen."

    old "In the past, they would have had to submit a written request, have it signed by a local lord, and then it would make its way into the bureaucracy of the state."
    new "In the past, they would have had to submit a written request, have it signed by a local lord, and then it would make its way into the bureaucracy of the state."

    old "From local lord, to provincal lord, to the court's secretary, and on and on."
    new "From local lord, to provincal lord, to the court's secretary, and on and on."

    old "It was a long and tiring process, mostly designed to filter out the endless trivial requests that people would submit."
    new "It was a long and tiring process, mostly designed to filter out the endless trivial requests that people would submit."

    old "But Sarah had only her army, and so instead, she suffered a request that by tradition, she was bound to hear."
    new "But Sarah had only her army, and so instead, she suffered a request that by tradition, she was bound to hear."

    old "Fine, offer up your petition, but make it quick."
    new "Fine, offer up your petition, but make it quick."

    old "The man stumbled forward, clearly already inebriated."
    new "The man stumbled forward, clearly already inebriated."

    old "He cleared his throat, doing his best to sound presentable."
    new "He cleared his throat, doing his best to sound presentable."

    old "Your Grace...your Highness...I..."
    new "Your Grace...your Highness...I..."

    old "Sarah gestured with her hands for him to move it along."
    new "Sarah gestured with her hands for him to move it along."

    old "We in this town have been faithful loyalists to your family."
    new "We in this town have been faithful loyalists to your family."

    old "And for it, we have paid dearly."
    new "And for it, we have paid dearly."

    old "Our town is to small to be permanently occupied, so each month, an emmissary from the Tribes rides out and hands out punishments."
    new "Our town is to small to be permanently occupied, so each month, an emmissary from the Tribes rides out and hands out punishments."

    old "Those who keep their heads down, are left alone."
    new "Those who keep their heads down, are left alone."

    old "Those who are loyal, are punished."
    new "Those who are loyal, are punished."

    old "He paused for a short while."
    new "He paused for a short while."

    old "And those who conspire with your enemies, who colaborate with the Tribes, they are rewarded."
    new "And those who conspire with your enemies, who colaborate with the Tribes, they are rewarded."

    old "They spy on their neighbours. Rat out loyalists. Condemn them and their families to suffer at the hand of the Tribes."
    new "They spy on their neighbours. Rat out loyalists. Condemn them and their families to suffer at the hand of the Tribes."

    old "And for it, the Tribes reward them."
    new "And for it, the Tribes reward them."

    old "She wasn't too surprised to learn of this. The Tribes had little interest in direct rule, they simply wanted to keep the populace down."
    new "She wasn't too surprised to learn of this. The Tribes had little interest in direct rule, they simply wanted to keep the populace down."

    old "This was an effective, not very costly, way of doing it."
    new "This was an effective, not very costly, way of doing it."

    old "I understand what you're saying, but what is your petition?"
    new "I understand what you're saying, but what is your petition?"

    old "The man gestured towards the far end of the tavern."
    new "The man gestured towards the far end of the tavern."

    old "Sarah saw the innkeeper, shaking. His face, pale."
    new "Sarah saw the innkeeper, shaking. His face, pale."

    old "That man...that man that served you your drink, and your food, he used to be little more than a farmhand and a thief."
    new "That man...that man that served you your drink, and your food, he used to be little more than a farmhand and a thief."

    old "No more than a few years ago, he travelled from town to town, begging for work, and stealing what he couldn't earn honestly."
    new "No more than a few years ago, he travelled from town to town, begging for work, and stealing what he couldn't earn honestly."

    old "A vagrant."
    new "A vagrant."

    old "Now, he looks all prim and proper, owner of this here tavern."
    new "Now, he looks all prim and proper, owner of this here tavern."

    old "But what he probably forgot to mention was that this tavern used to have a previous owner."
    new "But what he probably forgot to mention was that this tavern used to have a previous owner."

    old "A proper and rightious man, that held loyal to you and your family."
    new "A proper and rightious man, that held loyal to you and your family."

    old "And for that loyalty, the Tribesmen gave him the rope. They gave him the rope because this creature ratted him out."
    new "And for that loyalty, the Tribesmen gave him the rope. They gave him the rope because this creature ratted him out."

    old "And they gave him the tavern as a reward."
    new "And they gave him the tavern as a reward."

    old "The man stepped forward, anger growing on his face."
    new "The man stepped forward, anger growing on his face."

    old "On the far end of the room, Sarah saw the innkeeper, his entire body now shaking."
    new "On the far end of the room, Sarah saw the innkeeper, his entire body now shaking."

    old "A young woman had come out from the kitchen and stood next to him, a confused yet frightened expression on her face as well."
    new "A young woman had come out from the kitchen and stood next to him, a confused yet frightened expression on her face as well."

    old "You have come to our town. Liberated us from the yoke of the Tribesmen."
    new "You have come to our town. Liberated us from the yoke of the Tribesmen."

    old "I ask you...petition you...what kind of a country will you build?"
    new "I ask you...petition you...what kind of a country will you build?"

    old "Is it one where vermin like him live large? Or will you build a country as your Father did."
    new "Is it one where vermin like him live large? Or will you build a country as your Father did."

    old "One where justice rules, and men like him get what they deserve?"
    new "One where justice rules, and men like him get what they deserve?"

    old "Sarah saw everyone's eyes on her. A heavy silence growing deeper by the second."
    new "Sarah saw everyone's eyes on her. A heavy silence growing deeper by the second."

    old "The man and his friends were clearly drunk."
    new "The man and his friends were clearly drunk."

    old "Whatever justice they had in mind was likely not going to involve a judge."
    new "Whatever justice they had in mind was likely not going to involve a judge."

    old "Yet, if their story was true, then the innkeeper was a turncoat. A traitor that turned on her family the moment they fell out of power."
    new "Yet, if their story was true, then the innkeeper was a turncoat. A traitor that turned on her family the moment they fell out of power."

    old "What use did she have for subjects that would betray her the moment her rule weakened?"
    new "What use did she have for subjects that would betray her the moment her rule weakened?"

    old "And wasn't it right that a man who earned his fortune through treason, stood to lose it?"
    new "And wasn't it right that a man who earned his fortune through treason, stood to lose it?"

    old "Sarah saw the innkeeper, clutching the young woman, holding her close."
    new "Sarah saw the innkeeper, clutching the young woman, holding her close."

    old "Not his wife, she reasoned. His daughter."
    new "Not his wife, she reasoned. His daughter."

    old "Sarah paused for a moment longer, considering the case."
    new "Sarah paused for a moment longer, considering the case."

    old "The innkeeper might well deserve whatever came to him...but this was a mob. A mob asking for her approval."
    new "The innkeeper might well deserve whatever came to him...but this was a mob. A mob asking for her approval."

    old "And the mob would likely not spare the girl their wrath."
    new "And the mob would likely not spare the girl their wrath."

    old "Set the mob loose, let them have their revenge"
    new "Set the mob loose, let them have their revenge"

    old "She saw a smile creeping over the man's face."
    new "She saw a smile creeping over the man's face."

    old "Yes, my country will be one of justice."
    new "Yes, my country will be one of justice."

    old "And in my country, there will be no place for men that turn their backs on the Crown because it is easy."
    new "And in my country, there will be no place for men that turn their backs on the Crown because it is easy."

    old "Princess, please wait!"
    new "Princess, please wait!"

    old "Sarah saw the terrified expression on his face. On his daughter's face."
    new "Sarah saw the terrified expression on his face. On his daughter's face."

    old "My family has no use for fairweather subjects."
    new "My family has no use for fairweather subjects."

    old "You gained all of this through twisted means, and now you will face the consequences of your actions."
    new "You gained all of this through twisted means, and now you will face the consequences of your actions."

    old "And let it be known to everyone in Rosanna, that just because my family was driven from these lands, it does not change to whom you must be loyal."
    new "And let it be known to everyone in Rosanna, that just because my family was driven from these lands, it does not change to whom you must be loyal."

    old "The mob advanced on the innkeeper and his daughter, grabbing the both of them."
    new "The mob advanced on the innkeeper and his daughter, grabbing the both of them."

    old "Sarah heard them begin to yell."
    new "Sarah heard them begin to yell."

    old "As the mob advanced further, their yelling turned to begging screams."
    new "As the mob advanced further, their yelling turned to begging screams."

    old "Sarah watched as they dragged the both of them out of the tavern."
    new "Sarah watched as they dragged the both of them out of the tavern."

    old "By her word, the mob had been released, justified in their violent rage."
    new "By her word, the mob had been released, justified in their violent rage."

    old "Only later did Sarah receive the report of that night's events."
    new "Only later did Sarah receive the report of that night's events."

    old "The innkeeper had been tied to a pole outside."
    new "The innkeeper had been tied to a pole outside."

    old "Pelted with rocks, beaten with sticks, the townsfolk released their hatred."
    new "Pelted with rocks, beaten with sticks, the townsfolk released their hatred."

    old "No longer fearing retaliation from the Tribesmen, they were drunk on their power."
    new "No longer fearing retaliation from the Tribesmen, they were drunk on their power."

    old "The innkeeper was battered so badly, his skin turned purple as grape."
    new "The innkeeper was battered so badly, his skin turned purple as grape."

    old "He suffered on the edge of life and death before finally succumbing from his injuries."
    new "He suffered on the edge of life and death before finally succumbing from his injuries."

    old "His daughter suffered the mob's rage in her own way."
    new "His daughter suffered the mob's rage in her own way."

    old "Dragged out to one of the stables, the men took turns on her body, mixing their lust with their hatreds."
    new "Dragged out to one of the stables, the men took turns on her body, mixing their lust with their hatreds."

    old "Her sin was to be the daughter of a traitor, no more and no less."
    new "Her sin was to be the daughter of a traitor, no more and no less."

    old "In the end, they spared her from death, but the woman they had dragged from that tavern was forever changed."
    new "In the end, they spared her from death, but the woman they had dragged from that tavern was forever changed."

    old "Her father dead, her fortunes ruined, she would go on to live the life of an outcast."
    new "Her father dead, her fortunes ruined, she would go on to live the life of an outcast."

    old "The child she would carry, spawned from hatred, would inherit the traitor's mark of his mother."
    new "The child she would carry, spawned from hatred, would inherit the traitor's mark of his mother."

    old "Lives, for decades to come, shaped and warped by a moment of brutality."
    new "Lives, for decades to come, shaped and warped by a moment of brutality."

    old "And Sarah knew she had released it by uttering the word."
    new "And Sarah knew she had released it by uttering the word."

    old "Sarah would go on to live her own life, even as the lives of those too far beneath her consideration, suffered her verdict decades after."
    new "Sarah would go on to live her own life, even as the lives of those too far beneath her consideration, suffered her verdict decades after."

    old "Pain, suffering. It echoed out from a moment to several lifetimes."
    new "Pain, suffering. It echoed out from a moment to several lifetimes."

    old "A message, Sarah would try to rationalize. A warning to her enemies and those who broke their vows of loyalty."
    new "A message, Sarah would try to rationalize. A warning to her enemies and those who broke their vows of loyalty."

    old "Or perhaps, she had indulged the worst parts of her people."
    new "Or perhaps, she had indulged the worst parts of her people."

    old "And in doing so, stained her own soul as much as she had theirs."
    new "And in doing so, stained her own soul as much as she had theirs."

    old "But those would be considerations to come in years after."
    new "But those would be considerations to come in years after."

    old "For now, Sarah simply returned to the campaign map on her table, ignorant of the brutalities that would play out in the coming hours."
    new "For now, Sarah simply returned to the campaign map on her table, ignorant of the brutalities that would play out in the coming hours."

    old "Ignorant and blind."
    new "Ignorant and blind."

    old "Tell the mob to disband"
    new "Tell the mob to disband"

    old "Sarah stood up and shook her head."
    new "Sarah stood up and shook her head."

    old "Her voice roared."
    new "Her voice roared."

    old "No? You would deny us justice?!"
    new "No? You would deny us justice?!"

    old "Justice?"
    new "Justice?"

    old "You call this justice? To have a man and his daughter thrown to the wolves on your account?"
    new "You call this justice? To have a man and his daughter thrown to the wolves on your account?"

    old "I can bring in others to testify."
    new "I can bring in others to testify."

    old "Of course you can."
    new "Of course you can."

    old "You and the rest of your mob of frenzied men, seeking to settle a score."
    new "You and the rest of your mob of frenzied men, seeking to settle a score."

    old "Who would dare to disagree with you now?"
    new "Who would dare to disagree with you now?"

    old "She saw the anger on the man's face."
    new "She saw the anger on the man's face."

    old "I did not return to my homeland to settle cheap scores."
    new "I did not return to my homeland to settle cheap scores."

    old "I have a war to win, to liberate my country! I don't have time to waste on your petty squables!"
    new "I have a war to win, to liberate my country! I don't have time to waste on your petty squables!"

    old "Figures..."
    new "Figures..."

    old "Tribesmen. Roses. It's all the same shit. Not a one cares about the people."
    new "Tribesmen. Roses. It's all the same shit. Not a one cares about the people."

    old "The man stormed out, his gang following behind him."
    new "The man stormed out, his gang following behind him."

    old "Sarah saw one of her guards drawing his blade."
    new "Sarah saw one of her guards drawing his blade."

    old "She motioned him to stop."
    new "She motioned him to stop."

    old "Don't."
    new "Don't."

    old "He doesn't matter. Let him run his mouth. Not worth spilling blood over."
    new "He doesn't matter. Let him run his mouth. Not worth spilling blood over."

    old "The guard sheathed his blade again."
    new "The guard sheathed his blade again."

    old "Sarah sat back down at her table, returning her attention to the campaign map that was sprawled out."
    new "Sarah sat back down at her table, returning her attention to the campaign map that was sprawled out."

    old "She had work to do, and this distraction had already cost her more time than she was willing to waste."
    new "She had work to do, and this distraction had already cost her more time than she was willing to waste."

    old "Enforce your own justice"
    new "Enforce your own justice"

    old "No? You deny us a right to seek justice?"
    new "No? You deny us a right to seek justice?"

    old "Justice? You call this mob you've gathered justice?"
    new "Justice? You call this mob you've gathered justice?"

    old "I see your anger. It is perhaps rightious, but it is not justice."
    new "I see your anger. It is perhaps rightious, but it is not justice."

    old "Sarah looked across the room, anxious faces."
    new "Sarah looked across the room, anxious faces."

    old "Under my rule, there will be justice. Real justice."
    new "Under my rule, there will be justice. Real justice."

    old "Not handed out by violent mobs, but by verdict of the Crown that I represent."
    new "Not handed out by violent mobs, but by verdict of the Crown that I represent."

    old "Sarah pointed towards the innkeeper."
    new "Sarah pointed towards the innkeeper."

    old "If the man is guilty of what you say, he will be punished."
    new "If the man is guilty of what you say, he will be punished."

    old "But it will be my soldiers, acting on my word."
    new "But it will be my soldiers, acting on my word."

    old "And it will be him and him alone. Do you understand?"
    new "And it will be him and him alone. Do you understand?"

    old "The man nodded, seemingly placated."
    new "The man nodded, seemingly placated."

    old "Sarah gestured towards her guards."
    new "Sarah gestured towards her guards."

    old "Take the innkeeper, question him. If these claims of treason to the Crown are found to be true, hang him by dawn."
    new "Take the innkeeper, question him. If these claims of treason to the Crown are found to be true, hang him by dawn."

    old "The guards grabbed the innkeeper and dragged him away."
    new "The guards grabbed the innkeeper and dragged him away."

    old "The man, too scared to fight back, went quietly."
    new "The man, too scared to fight back, went quietly."

    old "For all of the night, the guards questioned him, testing his stories."
    new "For all of the night, the guards questioned him, testing his stories."

    old "At first, his excuses seemed probable."
    new "At first, his excuses seemed probable."

    old "But the more the guards pressed, asking about how he came to own the tavern, the more he stumbled."
    new "But the more the guards pressed, asking about how he came to own the tavern, the more he stumbled."

    old "When they began questioning other townsfolk, many came forward to confirm that he had earned the tavern by betraying the previous owner."
    new "When they began questioning other townsfolk, many came forward to confirm that he had earned the tavern by betraying the previous owner."

    old "Before dawn, more than a dozen witnesses all told the same story."
    new "Before dawn, more than a dozen witnesses all told the same story."

    old "The innkeeper, for his part, had stopped talking at all. Every excuse he came up with, turned against him."
    new "The innkeeper, for his part, had stopped talking at all. Every excuse he came up with, turned against him."

    old "As Sarah had ordered, when the sun crept across the horizon, the guards pulled the man into the town square."
    new "As Sarah had ordered, when the sun crept across the horizon, the guards pulled the man into the town square."

    old "With a rope, they hanged him from the roof of the inn he had stolen."
    new "With a rope, they hanged him from the roof of the inn he had stolen."

    old "Sarah had been busy, plotting her campaign, but took a brief minute to watch the execution."
    new "Sarah had been busy, plotting her campaign, but took a brief minute to watch the execution."

    old "The townsfolk seemed excited, as was often the case when an execution took place."
    new "The townsfolk seemed excited, as was often the case when an execution took place."

    old "But there seemed a real buzz in the air."
    new "But there seemed a real buzz in the air."

    old "Justice, they whispered, had returned. The rule of the Tribesmen would soon be over."
    new "Justice, they whispered, had returned. The rule of the Tribesmen would soon be over."

    old "Among the crowd, Sarah found only one face ruined by tears."
    new "Among the crowd, Sarah found only one face ruined by tears."

    old "The innkeepers daughter, held back by the guards that oversaw her father's execution."
    new "The innkeepers daughter, held back by the guards that oversaw her father's execution."

    old "Sarah couldn't help but feel sad for the girl, regardless of if her father had deserved his fate."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but feel sad for the girl, regardless of if her father had deserved his fate."

    old "A daughter loves her father, despite the quality of the man."
    new "A daughter loves her father, despite the quality of the man."

    old "Sarah hoped that at least, in speaking justice, she spared the girl from the mob."
    new "Sarah hoped that at least, in speaking justice, she spared the girl from the mob."

    old "Deciding on life and death."
    new "Deciding on life and death."

    old "This too would be part of wearing the crown, though to Sarah, it did not come easy."
    new "This too would be part of wearing the crown, though to Sarah, it did not come easy."

    old "By early next morning, Sarah's army had returned on the march."
    new "By early next morning, Sarah's army had returned on the march."

    old "The broken roads and heavy snowfall continued to plague the advance of her army."
    new "The broken roads and heavy snowfall continued to plague the advance of her army."

    old "Supplies were not yet an issue, but above all, Sarah feared the pace of their progress."
    new "Supplies were not yet an issue, but above all, Sarah feared the pace of their progress."

    old "At this rate, it might be weeks before they would reach the capital."
    new "At this rate, it might be weeks before they would reach the capital."

    old "Every day lost on a slow march, was a day more for the enemy to prepare."
    new "Every day lost on a slow march, was a day more for the enemy to prepare."

